    "narrative": "The Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is anchored today by **Corbin Carroll**, who sits in an elite tier with a score of 85.93. The combination of a highly favorable matchup against M\u00e1rquez (5.26 xERA) and the significant stolen base upside provided by a slow pitcher delivery creates the perfect environment for **Corbin Carroll** to exploit. Joining him as a high-floor play is **Seiya Suzuki** (69.54), whose strong score is bolstered by a potent wind-out factor and a favorable matchup against Sasaki. While **Seiya Suzuki** remains in a pending lineup status, his projected output remains significantly higher than the rest of the utility tier, making him a cornerstone for our production today.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the optimizer centered on the benching of **Alex Freeland** (49.73). Despite a solid profile, his projected slotting at the bottom of the order and a lower base efficiency forced him to the pine in favor of the higher-upside profiles like **Brice Turang** (65.39). **Brice Turang** earns his spot at the top of the lineup, where his elite lead-off status (+10% score adjustment) helps neutralize the risk posed by Keller. Meanwhile, we are monitoring the matchup for **Vinnie Pasquantino** (53.20); he faces a difficult assignment against Urena (2.35 xERA), but his strong platoon advantage keeps him viable as a UTIL play.\n\nRisk management remains a priority given the volatility of our \"lineup pending\" spots for **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Seiya Suzuki**, and **Giancarlo Stanton**. We have already removed **Mickey Moniak** from active consideration due to a confirmed rainout, ensuring we don't waste game caps on zeros. While **Austin Riley** was considered, his difficult matchup against a top-tier arm in Wheeler caused his score to plummet, keeping him benched alongside **Jose Caballero**. We will continue to evaluate if any late-breaking lineup changes for **Dalton Rushing**, **Josh Naylor**, **Trevor Story**, **Max Muncy**, **James Wood**, or **Tyler Soderstrom** require further tactical pivots before first pitch.",
